                "invention-title": [
                    "Mine low-carbon energy system based on multi-element energy storage",
                    "基于多元储能的矿井低碳能源系统"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The mine low-carbon energy system comprises a power generation module, the power generation module is connected with a battery energy storage unit, an electrolytic cell, an electric boiler and an energy storage conversion motor through wires, an output shaft of the energy storage conversion motor is sequentially connected with a turbine and a compressor, and a heat storage device is connected between the turbine and the compressor. The output end of the turbine is connected with a cold storage tank through a pipeline, the cold storage tank is connected with a preheater, the preheater is connected with a compressor, the electrolytic bath is connected with a hydrogen storage tank and an oxygen storage tank through pipelines, the oxygen storage tank is connected with a fuel cell, and the electric boiler and the fuel cell are connected with a heat storage device through pipelines. The problem that in the prior art, an existing mine energy system is still mainly based on an external regional power grid, and mining area new energy is self-consumed after large-scale access is solved."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开的基于多元储能的矿井低碳能源系统，包括发电模块，发电模块通过导线分别连接有电池储能、电解槽、电锅炉与储能转化电机，储能转化电机输出轴依次连接有透平与压缩机，透平与压缩机之间连接有储热装置，透平输出端通过管道连接有蓄冷罐，蓄冷罐连接有预热器，预热器与压缩机连接，电解槽通过管道分别连接有储氢罐和储氧罐，储氧罐连接有燃料电池，电锅炉与燃料电池分别通过管道与储热装置连接。解决了现有技术中存在的目前矿井能源系统仍以外部区域电网为主，矿区新能源大规模接入后自我消纳的问题。"
                }
            ]
